Get an AnalysisEngine from the name (Java-style, dotted) of an XML descriptor file, and a set of configuration parameters.

Parameters:
descriptorName - The fully qualified, Java-style, dotted name of the XML descriptor file.
parameters - Any additional configuration parameters to be set. These should be supplied as (name, value) pairs, so there should always be an even number of parameters.
Returns:
The AnalysisEngine created from the XML descriptor and the configuration parameters.

createAnalysisEngine

public static AnalysisEngine createAnalysisEngine(java.lang.Class<? extends AnalysisComponent> componentClass,
                                                  TypeSystemDescription typeSystem,
                                                  java.lang.Object... configurationParameters)
                                           throws ResourceInitializationException
Get an AnalysisEngine from an AnalysisComponent class, a type system and a set of configuration parameters.

Parameters:
componentClass - The class of the AnalysisComponent to be created as an AnalysisEngine.
typeSystem - A description of the types used by the AnalysisComponent (may be null).
configurationParameters - Any additional configuration parameters to be set. These should be supplied as (name, value) pairs, so there should always be an even number of parameters.
Returns:
The AnalysisEngine created from the AnalysisComponent class and initialized with the type system and the configuration parameters.
Throws:
ResourceInitializationException

Creates an AnalysisEngine from the given descriptor, and uses the engine to process the file or text.

Parameters:
descriptorFileName - The fully qualified, Java-style, dotted name of the XML descriptor file.
fileNameOrText - Either the path of a file to be loaded, or a string to use as the text. If the string given is not a valid path in the file system, it will be assumed to be text.
Returns:
A JCas object containing the processed document.
